Pre-Game Insights: South Africa has a better chance to win this fixture and defeat Pakistan to register their fifth win in the ICC ODI World Cup 2023.
Proteas batting has been a massive strength with players like Quinton de Kock, Henrich Klassen, and Aiden Markram scoring fluently.
Pakistan's batting has struggled for consistency and their bowling has been toothless in the tournament.
Temba Bavuma and Lungi Ngidi missed the previous game against Bangladesh due to injury.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The MA Chidambaram Stadium in Chennai has produced balanced wickets with an average score of 245, suitable for both batting and bowling.
Fast bowlers can generate movement and bounce, while spinners find wickets as the ball grips.
